#Text=The Washington Wizards ( 6 - 4 ) escaped with a 97 - 95 victory over the Detroit Pistons ( 7 - 6 ) on Saturday .
#Text=This was a spectacular game from start to finish , as it was nip - and - tuck throughout .
#Text=The only major differential in the stat sheet were the steal totals , as Washington had 10 compared to Detroit 's three .
#Text=The benches were also a big difference in the game , as the Wizards got 51 bench points while the Pistons got just 15 .
#Text=If this does end up being a playoff matchup down the line , it would be a heck of a series .
#Text=The Wizards didn’t get their best performances from John Wall and Bradley Beal , but the “others” played well here and carried them to a win .
#Text=In fact , Wall and Beal combined for just 15 points , seven assists , three rebounds and three steals in the win .
#Text=This was Beal 's first game in two weeks after sufffering a shoulder injury , so ithe poor game is nothing to be concerned with .
#Text=The two best players for Washington on this night were Nene Hilario and Ramon Sessions .
#Text=Nene tallied 18 points , seven rebounds , two assists and two steals in the win , while going 9 - for - 10 from the field .
#Text=Sessions was great as well , as he totaled 14 points , nine assists and four rebounds off the bench .
#Text=This is a deeper team than in years past and that may be exactly what they need to be successful .
#Text=The Wizards will look to keep up their winning ways against the Indiana Pacers on Tuesday .
#Text=The Pistons played all their starters at least 32 minutes and they fell just short on Saturday .
#Text=Every starter scored at least 16 points , except for Andre Drummond who tallied eight points and 13 rebounds in the defeat .
#Text=The Pistons best player on this night was Marcus Morris , who collected 18 points , nine rebounds and four assists in the loss .
#Text=Reggie Jackson contributed 20 points and nine assists , but committed six turnovers in an up - and - down performance .
#Text=This was a tough loss , but it 's a good sign to see them compete so hard with the Eastern Conference elite .
#Text=The Pistons will look to bounce - back against the struggling Milwaukee Bucks on Monday .
